Hey Alexis:

You cannot reach the GUI through the firewall?  I&#39;d think that this at 
least should work.

In standalone mode, Heritrix registers itself with the JVM&#39;s JMX Agent.  
The latter is enabled by the heritrix startup script.   Port 8080 is the 
default GUI listener.  Port 8849 is the what we&#39;ve asked the JVM&#39;s JMX 
Agent to listen for connections on.  The third port is a randomly chosen 
location for the JMX RMI server (Baseline JMX communication protocol 
runs over RMI).  If we put up our own JMX Agent rather than leverage the 
JVM&#39;s, we could stop the RMI server port numbering wandering.  Grep 
&#39;firewall&#39; in this page: 
http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/technotes/guides/management/agent.html#gdfvq.

St.Ack



